<item>
            <title>[QPID-5978] [Java Client] Failure to negotiate SSL in AMQP 0-8/9/9-1 (e.g. because of an invalid certificate) causes a 30s delay before failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-5978</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While looking at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-5960&quot; title=&quot;ssl_verify_hostname should default to true rather than false&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPID-5960&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPID-5960&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I found that attempting to connect to a broker with an invalid certificate using AMQP 0-9-1, the connection attempt would wait for 30s and then fail with a timeout exception - with no information on the underlying cause.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same symptoms can be seen when attempting to connect using SSL to a non-SSL port...  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
